{
  "$comment": "The polished Flow — a Container tree of Groups (Sections/SubSections) and Pages referencing obligations by UUID id (obligations.md:929-965). Pages carry ordered `presents` / `presentsForEach` entries; each entry owns the pinned presentation copy (label, hint, option labels) because obligation records carry none. Per Rulings item 3 (2026-07-02) `fullName` is the ONLY page-hard mandate in the whole Flow — every other parity required_at_save field is authored page-soft and enforced as engine-mandatory at CYA POST. PROVISIONAL schema picks, labelled per OPEN2-1/OPEN2-2/ARCH-22: (1) `presentsForEach` is an ARRAY of entries (the doc sketches a single object) so one page can project several indexed obligations sharing fulfilment ids; (2) CheckYourAnswers and Confirmation are top-level constructs OUTSIDE the Section tree (obligations.md:959 'special; not a Section'); (3) the get-your-quote Section carries the `quoteReady` appliesWhen name while the hub renders it always-visible-inert (parity ruling c — a documented deviation from doc-default NA-hiding); (4) `revealedBy` on a presents entry pins the govuk conditional-reveal composition (excessAmount under the voluntaryExcess Yes radio). Copy is lifted verbatim from spike-a templates/config (the parity checklist is parity-facts.json).",
